<i>noun</i>: 충전 [충전], 진정 [진ː정], 이완 [이완], 완화 [완ː화], 안식 [안식] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt>충전 [충전]</dt><br>
<dd>1. recharging</dd><br>
<dd>건전지 등에 전기를 채워 넣는 일.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of filling up electricity in a battery, etc.</dd><br>
<dd>2. refreshment; relaxation</dd><br>
<dd>(비유적으로) 쉬면서 기운을 되찾거나 실력을 쌓는 일.</dd><br>
<dd>(figurative) An act of taking some time off from work and recovering one's energy or developing one's capabilities.</dd><br>
<dt>진정 [진ː정]</dt><br>
<dd>1. settlement</dd><br>
<dd>시끄럽고 어지러운 분위기를 가라앉힘.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of calming a noisy, chaotic atmosphere.</dd><br>
<dd>2. relaxation; soothing</dd><br>
<dd>몹시 흥분된 감정이나 아픔 등을 가라앉힘.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of soothing one's agitated feeling, pain, etc.</dd><br>
<dt>이완 [이완]</dt><br>
<dd>1. relaxation</dd><br>
<dd>바짝 긴장되어 있던 정신이나 분위기가 풀림.</dd><br>
<dd>The process of one's mental strain or a tense atmosphere easing.</dd><br>
<dd>2. relaxation</dd><br>
<dd>굳어서 뻣뻣해진 근육이 풀림.</dd><br>
<dd>The process of a hardened, stiff muscle untightening.</dd><br>
<dt>완화 [완ː화]</dt><br>
<dd>1. relaxation; easing</dd><br>
<dd>긴장된 상태나 매우 급한 것을 느슨하게 함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of relaxing something tense or stressful.</dd><br>
<dd>2. relief; alleviation</dd><br>
<dd>병의 증상이 약해짐.</dd><br>
<dd>For the symptoms of a disease to be assuaged.</dd><br>
<dt>안식 [안식]</dt><br>
<dd>rest; repose; relaxation</dd><br>
<dd>편히 쉼.</dd><br>
<dd>Taking a goof rest.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>